title: Scan error – can't scan items - shows error message
text: If you get an error when trying to scan items (can be something like "Scanned items may not be less than zero") and the item cant be found manually, try the following: 1. Log into the POS 2. Click on Support Tools icon (screen with wrench). 3. Choose store, machine and change this machine only 4. Choose Search parameters 5. Grab one of the options above the black line with the mouse and pull it down. 6. Click Save 7. Pull the moved option back to it's previous placement. 8. Click Save 9. Reload the POS program. That should fix it.
description:
If you get an error when trying to scan items (can be something like "Scanned items may not be less than zero") and the item cant be found manually, try the following: 

  

  1. 1. Log into the POS 

  

  1. 2. Click on Support Tools icon (screen with wrench). 

  

 

  

  

  1. 3. Choose store, machine and change this machine only 

  

 

  

  1. 4. Choose Search parameters 

  

 

  

  1. 5. Grab one of the options above the black line with the mouse and pull it down. 

  

 

  

  1. 6. Click Save 

  

  1. 7. Pull the moved option back to it's previous placement. 

  

  1. 8. Click Save 

  

  1. 9. Reload the POS program. 

  

That should fix it.

title: Scan error - Object reference not set error
text: If the client tries to scan items on POS and gets this error message It means that the currency they use is not defined and needs to be set up first.
description:
If the client tries to scan items on POS and gets this error message 

  

 

  

It means that the currency they use is not defined and needs to be set up first.

title: Scan error – shows strange signs when scanning items
text: Usually means that CapsLoc (capital letters) is on. Ask client to press the CapsLoc (Umschalttaste) on the keyboard and try again.
description: Usually means that CapsLoc (capital letters) is on. Ask client to press the CapsLoc (Umschalttaste) on the keyboard and try again.

title: Scan error - StartIndex Error
text: First try to type Restart in the Shop Assistant field and click the green button. This will restart the POS program. If this doesn't help, try the following steps: 1. Log into POS with an administrator account. 2. Click Screen with Wrench button 3. Choose store and machine 4. Click Search Parameters 5. Grab e.g. Season with the mouse and pull it below the black line. Release, click save, grab it and pull it back above the black line, release, click save 6. Click close 7. Click cancel sale 8. Type reload in the Shop assistant field Now it should work On very rare occasions, none of the above work. In this case, restoring the database will work.
description:
First try to type Restart in the Shop Assistant field and click the green button. This will restart the POS program. 


 

  

If this doesn't help, try the following steps: 

  

  1. 1. Log into POS with an administrator account. 

  

  1. 2. Click Screen with Wrench button 

  

  1. 3. Choose store and machine 

  

  1. 4. Click Search Parameters 

  

 

  

  1. 5. Grab e.g. Season with the mouse and pull it below the black line. Release, click save, grab it and pull it back above the black line, release, click save 

  

  1. 6. Click close 

  

  

 

  

  1. 7. Click cancel sale 

  

 

  

  1. 8. Type reload in the Shop assistant field 

  

 

  

Now it should work 

  

On very rare occasions, none of the above work. 

  

In this case, restoring the database will work.
